                        "correctAnswerIndex": 2,
                        "correctFeedback": "Correct! The key \"banana\" has the value 0.75.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Look up the key \"banana\" to find its value.",
                        "explanation": "prices[\"banana\"] returns the value associated with the key \"banana\", which is 0.75."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "key_errors",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**Be careful!** If you try to access a key that doesn't exist, you'll get an error."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "student = {\"name\": \"Alice\", \"age\": 20}\nprint(student[\"grade\"])",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Error: KeyError: 'grade'"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The key `\"grade\"` doesn't exist in the dictionary, causing an error."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "get_method",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "To avoid errors, use the `get(key)` method. It returns `None` if the key doesn't exist."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "student = {\"name\": \"Alice\", \"age\": 20}\ngrade = student.get(\"grade\")\nprint(grade)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "None"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "`get()` returns `None` instead of causing an error."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "get_with_default",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can also provide a default value as the second argument to `get(key, default_value)`. The first argument is the key you want to look up, and the second argument is the value that will be returned if the key does not exist in the dictionary."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "student = {\"name\": \"Alice\", \"age\": 20}\ngrade = student.get(\"grade\", \"No grade\")\nprint(grade)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "No grade"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Since `\"grade\"` doesn't exist, `get()` returns the default value `\"No grade\"`."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_get",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "code_fill",
                    "content": "Use `get()` to safely access the `\"email\"` key with default `\"No email\"`.",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "lines": [
                            {
                                "code": "user = {\"name\": \"Bob\", \"age\": 30}",
                                "indent": 0
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "email = user.{1}({2}, {3})",
                                "indent": 0,
                                "blank": "1,2,3"
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "print(email)",
                                "indent": 0
                            }
                        ],
                        "options": [
                            "\"email\"",
                            "get",
                            "\"No email\""
                        ],
                        "solutions": {
                            "1": "get",
                            "2": "\"email\"",
                            "3": "\"No email\""
                        },
                        "hint": "Use get(key, default_value) to access safely.",
                        "correctFeedback": "Perfect! get() returns the default when the key doesn't exist.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Use get(\"email\", \"No email\") to provide a default value.",
                        "explanation": "get() is safer than brackets because it won't cause an error if the key is missing.",
                        "output": "No email"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "checking_keys",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can check if a key exists using the `in` operator."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "student = {\"name\": \"Alice\", \"age\": 20}\nprint(\"name\" in student)\nprint(\"grade\" in student)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "True\nFalse"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "`\"name\"` exists in the dictionary (returns `True`), but `\"grade\"` doesn't (returns `False`)."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_in",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "code_fill",
                    "content": "Check if `\"price\"` exists in the dictionary before accessing it.",
                    "properties": {
